        </div>
        <div class="row time">
            <div class="col-2 date">Sep 14, 2017</div>
            <div class="col-10 description">Association for Democratic Reforms, a NGO and lead petitioner moves Supreme
                Court challenging scheme.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="row time">
            <div class="col-2 date">Oct 03, 2017</div>
            <div class="col-10 description">Supreme Court issues notices to Centre Government and Election Commission on
                PIL filed by the NGO.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="row time">
            <div class="col-2 date">Jan 2, 2018</div>
            <div class="col-10 description">The Central Government notifies the Electoral Bond Scheme.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="row time">
            <div class="col-2 date">Nov 7, 2022</div>
            <div class="col-10 description">The Electoral Bond Scheme was amended to increase the sale days from 70 to
                85 in a year where any assembly election may be scheduled.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="row time">
            <div class="col-2 date">Oct 16, 2023</div>
            <div class="col-10 description">Supreme Court bench headed by CJI DY Chandrachud refers pleas against the
                scheme to five judge Constitution bench.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="row time">
            <div class="col-2 date">Oct 31, 2023</div>
            <div class="col-10 description">A five judge Constitution bench headed by CJI DY Chandrachud commences
                hearing on pelas against the scheme.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="row time">
            <div class="col-2 date">Nov 2, 2023</div>
            <div class="col-10 description">Supreme Court reserves verdict.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="row time">
            <div class="col-2 date">Feb 15, 2024</div>
            <div class="col-10 description">Supreme Court delivers unanimous judgement annulling the scheme, saying it
                violates Constitutional right to freedom of speech and expression as well as the right to information.
                And ask SBI to submit the data of Donor and Purchaser to EC by March 06, 2024.
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row time">
            <div class="col-2 date">March 04, 2024</div>
            <div class="col-10 description">SBI filed application to Supreme Court seeking an extention until June 30,
                2024 to furnish the details. </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row time">
            <div class="col-2 date">March 11, 2024</div>
            <div class="col-10 description">Supreme Court dismiss the SBI's plea for extention, says disclose the
                information by March 12, 2024</div>
        </div>
        <div class="row time">
            <div class="col-2 date">March 12, 2024</div>
            <div class="col-10 description">SBI only discloses Purchaser Name, Date of Purchase, Denominations in one file and Party Name, Date of Encashment and Denominations in second file.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="row time">
            <div class="col-2 date">March 18, 2024</div>
            <div class="col-10 description">The Court directed SBI to disclose all the details that it has stored
                concerning the Electoral Bonds transactions. To ensure there is no more contempt of the Court’s Order,
                the Bench also stated that the SBI’s Chairman must file an affidavit confirming full disclosure by 5:00
                pm on 21 March 2024.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="row time">
            <div class="col-2 date">March 21, 2024</div>
            <div class="col-10 description">SBI submit the data to Election Commission and ECI uploded the data on its website.</div>
